metadata.name: Uranium Waste
metadata.description:
The by-product of consuming Uranium Fuel Rods in the Nuclear Power Plant.
Non-fissile Uranium can be extracted. Handle with caution.
Caution: HIGHLY Radioactive.

metadata.name: Plutonium Waste
metadata.description:
The by-product of consuming Plutonium Fuel Rods in the Nuclear Power Plant.
Needs to be stored in a safe location. Handle with caution.
Caution: EXTREMELY Radioactive.

metadata.name: Battery
metadata.description: Primarily used as fuel for Drones and Vehicles.

metadata.name: Aluminum Ingot
metadata.description:
Aluminum Ingots are made from Aluminum Scrap, which is refined from Alumina Solution.
Used to produce specialized aluminum-based parts.

metadata.name: Color Cartridge
metadata.description:
Used for applying Patterns to structures with the Customizer.
(Patterns can be purchased in the AWESOME Shop.)
metadata.unlockedBy:
[[Flower Petals Research|MAM Flower Petals Research]] - Color Cartridges OR
[[Tier 2]] - Resource Sink Bonus Program

metadata.name: Cable
metadata.description:
Used for crafting.
Primarily used to build power lines.

metadata.name: Concrete
metadata.description:
Used for building.
Good for stable foundations.

metadata.name: Modular Frame
metadata.description:
Used for crafting.
Multi-purpose building block.

metadata.name: Steel Beam
metadata.description: Steel Beams are used most often when constructing a little more advanced buildings.

metadata.name: Non-fissile Uranium
metadata.description:
The isotope Uranium-238 is non-fissile, meaning it cannot be used for nuclear fission. It can, however, be converted into fissile Plutonium in the Particle Accelerator.
Caution: Mildly Radioactive.

metadata.name: Plutonium Pellet
metadata.description:
Produced in the Particle Accelerator through conversion of Non-fissile Uranium.
Used to produce Encased Plutonium Cells for Plutonium Fuel Rods.
Power Usage: 250-750 MW (500 MW average).
Caution: Moderately Radioactive.

metadata.name: Encased Plutonium Cell
metadata.description:
Plutonium Cells are concrete encased Plutonium Pellets.
Used to produce Plutonium Fuel Rods for Nuclear Power production.
Caution: Moderately Radioactive.

metadata.name: Silica
metadata.description: Derived from Raw Quartz. Commonly used to create glass structures, advanced refinement processes, and alternative production of electronics.
metadata.unlockedBy:
[[Quartz Research|MAM Quartz Research]] - Silica OR
[[Tier 7]] - Bauxite Refinement

metadata.name: Iron Plate

Used for crafting.

Mucus from the power slugs compressed into a solid crystal-like shard.
It radiates a strange power.

One of the most basic parts.

metadata.description: A much more efficient alternative to Coal. Used as fuel for vehicles and coal generators.

metadata.unlockedBy:

[[Tier 5]] - Alternative Fluid Transport

metadata.name: Turbofuel
metadata.description: A more efficient alternative to Fuel. Can be used to generate power or packaged to be used as fuel for Vehicles.

metadata.name: Packaged Turbofuel
metadata.description: Turbofuel, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for Vehicles and the Jetpack.

metadata.name: Circuit Board
metadata.description: Circuit Boards are advanced electronics that are used in a plethora of different ways.

metadata.name: Plastic
metadata.description: A versatile and easy to manufacture material that can be used for a lot of things.

metadata.name: Motor
metadata.description: The Motor creates a mechanical force that is used to move things from machines to vehicles.

metadata.name: Encased Industrial Beam
metadata.description:
Encased Industrial Beams utilizes the compressive strength of concrete and tensile strength of steel simultaneously.
Mostly used as a stable basis for constructing buildings.

metadata.name: Steel Pipe
metadata.description: Steel Pipes are used most often when constructing a little more advanced buildings.

metadata.name: Rubber
metadata.description: Rubber is a material that is very flexible and has a lot of friction.

metadata.name: Fuel
metadata.description: Fuel can be used to generate power or packaged to be used as fuel for Vehicles or the Jetpack.
metadata.unlockedBy:
[[Tier 5]] - Oil Processing OR
[[Tier 5]] - Alternative Fluid Transport

metadata.name: Polymer Resin
metadata.description:
Used for crafting.
A by-product of oil refinement into fuel. Commonly used to manufacture plastics.

metadata.name: Petroleum Coke
metadata.description:
Used for crafting.
A carbon-rich material distilled from Heavy Oil Residue.
Used as a less efficient coal replacement.

metadata.name: Steel Ingot
metadata.description: Steel Ingots are made from Iron Ore that's been smelted with Coal. They are made into several parts used in building construction.

metadata.name: Versatile Framework
metadata.description: Project Part #2. Ship with the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

metadata.name: Heavy Modular Frame
metadata.description: A more robust multi-purpose frame.

metadata.name: Packaged Fuel
metadata.description: Fuel, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for Vehicles and the Jetpack.

metadata.name: Packaged Oil
metadata.description: Crude Oil, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for Vehicles.

metadata.name: Packaged Heavy Oil Residue
metadata.description: Heavy Oil Residue, packaged for alternative transport. Can be used as fuel for Vehicles.

metadata.name: Packaged Water
metadata.description: Water, packaged for alternative transport.

metadata.name: Copper Ingot
metadata.description:
Used for crafting.
Crafted into the most basic parts.

metadata.name: Quartz Crystal
metadata.description: Derived from Raw Quartz. Used in the production of advanced radar technology and high-quality display screens.
metadata.unlockedBy:
[[Quartz Research|MAM Quartz Research]] - Quartz Crystals OR
[[Tier 7]] - Bauxite Refinement

metadata.name: Caterium Ingot
metadata.description: Caterium Ingots are smelted from Caterium Ore. Caterium Ingots are mostly used for advanced electronics.

metadata.name: Aluminum Scrap
metadata.description: Aluminum Scrap is pure aluminum refined from Alumina. Can be smelted down to Aluminum Ingots for industrial usage.

metadata.name: Sulfuric Acid
metadata.description: A mineral acid produced by combining Sulfur and Water in a complex reaction. Primarily used in refinement processes and Battery production.

metadata.name: Encased Uranium Cell
metadata.description:
Uranium Cells are produced from Uranium Ore.
Used to produce Uranium Fuel Rods for Nuclear Power production.
Caution: Mildly Radioactive.

metadata.name: Heat Sink
metadata.description: Used to dissipate heat faster.

metadata.name: Cooling System
metadata.description: Used to keep temperatures of advanced parts and buildings from exceeding to inefficient levels.

metadata.name: Nitric Acid
metadata.description: Produced by reaction of Nitrogen Gas with Water. Its high corrosiveness and oxidizing properties make it an excellent choice for refinement and fuel production processes.

metadata.name: Aluminum Casing
metadata.description: A versatile container cast from Aluminum Ingots.

metadata.name: Radio Control Unit
metadata.description: Enhances and directs radio signals.

metadata.name: Alclad Aluminum Sheet
metadata.description: Thin, lightweight, and highly durable sheets mainly used for products that require high heat conduction or a high specific strength.

metadata.name: Computer
metadata.description: A Computer is a complex logic machine that is used to control advanced behavior in machines.

metadata.name: Crystal Oscillator
metadata.description: A crystal oscillator is an electronic oscillator circuit that uses the mechanical resonance of a vibrating crystal to create an electrical signal with a precise frequency.
metadata.unlockedBy:
[[Quartz Research|MAM Quartz Research]] - Crystal Oscillator OR
[[Tier 7]] - Bauxite Refinement

metadata.name: Alumina Solution
metadata.description: Dissolved Alumina, extracted from Bauxite. Can be further refined into Aluminum Scrap for Aluminum Ingot production.

metadata.name: Smart Plating
metadata.description: Project Part #1. Ship with the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

metadata.name: High-Speed Connector
metadata.description: The high-speed connector connects several cables and wires in a very efficient way. Uses a standard pattern so its applications are many and varied.
metadata.unlockedBy:
[[Caterium Research|MAM Caterium Research]] - High-Speed Connector OR
[[Tier 7]] - Aeronautical Engineering

metadata.name: Automated Wiring
metadata.description: Project Part #3. Ship with the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

metadata.name: Stator

The static parts of a motor.

metadata.unlockedBy:
[[Caterium Research|MAM Caterium Research]] - AI Limiter OR
[[Tier 7]] - Aeronautical Engineering

metadata.name: Quickwire
metadata.description: Caterium's high conductivity and resistance to corrosion makes it ideal for small, advanced electronics.

metadata.name: Modular Engine
metadata.description: Project Part #4. Ship with the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

metadata.name: Adaptive Control Unit
metadata.description: Project Part #5. Ship with the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.

metadata.name: Turbo Motor
metadata.description: The Turbo Motor is a more complex and more powerful version of the regular Motor.

metadata.name: Pressure Conversion Cube
metadata.description: Converts outgoing force into internal pressure. Required to contain unstable, high-energy matter.

metadata.name: Fused Modular Frame
metadata.description: A corrosion resistant, nitride hardened, highly robust, yet lightweight modular frame.

metadata.name: Supercomputer
metadata.description: The supercomputer is the next-gen version of the computer.
metadata.unlockedBy:
[[Caterium Research|MAM Caterium Research]] - Supercomputer OR
[[Tier 7]] - Aeronautical Engineering

metadata.name: Electromagnetic Control Rod
metadata.description: Control Rods regulate power output via electromagnetism.

metadata.name: Copper Powder
metadata.description:
Ground down Copper Ingots.
The high natural density of Copper, combined with the granularity of the powder, makes this part fit for producing Nuclear Pasta in the Particle Accelerator.

metadata.name: Empty Fluid Tank
metadata.description: Used to package gases and volatile liquids for transportation.
metadata.unlockedBy:
[[Tier 8]] - Advanced Aluminum Production OR
[[Tier 8]] - Particle Enrichment

metadata.name: Nuclear Pasta
metadata.description:
Project Part #9. Ship with the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.
Power Usage: 500-1500 MW (1000 MW average).
Nuclear Pasta is extremely dense degenerate matter, formed when extreme pressure forces protons and electrons together into neutrons. It is theorized to exist naturally within the crust of neutron stars.

metadata.name: Assembly Director System
metadata.description:
Project Part #6. Ship with the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.
This extremely fast and precise computing system is specifically designed to direct the Project Assembly: Assembly Phase.

metadata.name: Magnetic Field Generator
metadata.description:
Project Part #7. Ship with the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.
These modular generators use superconducting magnets and vast amounts of electricity to produce an easily expandable and powerful magnetic field.

metadata.name: Thermal Propulsion Rocket
metadata.description:
Project Part #8. Ship with the Space Elevator to complete phases of Project Assembly.
Uses extreme heat to produce the high-pressure plasma required to get Project Assembly into motion.

metadata.name: Black Powder
metadata.description: An explosive powder that is commonly used to produce simple explosives.

metadata.name: Gas Filter
metadata.description: Used in the Gas Mask to filter out toxins and pollutants from the air.

metadata.name: Iodine Infused Filter
metadata.description: Used in the Hazmat Suit to absorb radioactive particles.

metadata.name: Alien Protein
metadata.description:
Ground down Alien Remains in a neat little package.
Used for medical purposes and to research alien organisms.
metadata.unlockedBy:
[[Alien Organisms Research|MAM Alien Organisms Research]] - Hog Research OR
[[Alien Organisms Research|MAM Alien Organisms Research]] - Hatcher Research OR
[[Alien Organisms Research|MAM Alien Organisms Research]] - Spitter Research OR
[[Alien Organisms Research|MAM Alien Organisms Research]] - Stinger Research

metadata.name: Alien DNA Capsule
metadata.description:
This data capsule translates organic chemicals into readable alien genetics information.
Used for researching alien organisms.
Go the extra kilometer! Knowledge is power, and power is just efficiency with fewer steps. Depositing Alien DNA Capsules in the AWESOME Sink provides FICSIT with knowledge, and Pioneers with Coupons.
metadata.unlockedBy: [[Alien Organisms Research|MAM Alien Organisms Research]] - Bio-Organic Properties

metadata.name: Purple Power Slug
metadata.description: A strange slug radiating a powerful strange power.

metadata.name: Yellow Power Slug
metadata.description: A strange slug radiating a strange power.

metadata.name: Blue Power Slug
metadata.description: A strange slug radiating a weak strange power.

metadata.name: Smokeless Powder
metadata.description: An explosive powder that is commonly used to produce modern firearms.

metadata.name: FICSMAS Wonder Star
metadata.description: This special FICSMAS Star signifies the productivity of FICSIT all across the universe. It also signifies the fact that you have nearly completed the Holiday Event, so it's time to get back to work.
metadata.unlockedBy: [[FICSMAS Holiday Event Research|MAM FICSMAS Holiday Event Research]] - FICSMAS Wreath

metadata.name: FICSMAS Ornament Bundle

metadata.unlockedBy: [[FICSMAS Holiday Event Research|MAM FICSMAS Holiday Event Research]] - FICSMAS Lights

metadata.name: FICSMAS Decoration
metadata.description: A decoration used to make decorations. Its use cases are questionable.
metadata.unlockedBy: [[FICSMAS Holiday Event Research|MAM FICSMAS Holiday Event Research]] - It's snowing!

metadata.name: Candy Cane
metadata.description:
A delicious Candy Cane to be enjoyed during the FICSMAS Holidays.
*Disclaimer: Can't be consumed...

metadata.name: Actual Snow
metadata.description: It's snow. Not the nice, thick, crunchy kind though... more the disgustingly wet, slushy kind... Guess we can make stuff from it.
metadata.unlockedBy: [[FICSMAS Holiday Event Research|MAM FICSMAS Holiday Event Research]] - A friend

metadata.name: FICSMAS Bow
metadata.description: A fancy Bow, maybe someone can wear this? You certainly can't! Probably, some parts and decorations can be made from this.
metadata.unlockedBy: [[FICSMAS Holiday Event Research|MAM FICSMAS Holiday Event Research]] - Candy Cane Decor

metadata.name: Copper FICSMAS Ornament

metadata.unlockedBy: [[FICSMAS Holiday Event Research|MAM FICSMAS Holiday Event Research]] - FICSMAS Gift Tree

metadata.name: FICSMAS Tree Branch

metadata.unlockedBy: [[FICSMAS Holiday Event Research|MAM FICSMAS Holiday Event Research]] - FICSMAS Tree Base

metadata.name: Red FICSMAS Ornament

Used for crafting.
Basic resource mainly used for electricity.

metadata.name: Caterium Ore
metadata.description: Caterium Ore is smelted into Caterium Ingots. Caterium Ingots are mostly used for advanced electronics.

metadata.name: Uranium
metadata.description:
Uranium is a radioactive element.
Used to produce Encased Uranium Cells for Uranium Fuel Rods.
Caution: Moderately Radioactive.

metadata.name: Nitrogen Gas
metadata.description: Nitrogen can be used in a variety of ways, such as metallurgy, cooling, and Nitric Acid production. On Massage-2(AB)b, it can be extracted from underground gas wells.

metadata.name: Bauxite
metadata.description: Bauxite is used to produce Alumina, which can be further refined into the Aluminum Scrap required to produce Aluminum Ingots.

metadata.name: Xeno-Zapper
metadata.description: Standard issue electroshock self-defense weapon for melee range.

metadata.name: Xeno-Basher
metadata.description: Heavy electroshock self-defense weapon for melee range.

metadata.name: Candy Cane Basher
metadata.description:
Slot: Hands
Heavy delicious self defense weapon for melee range.
metadata.unlockedBy: [[FICSMAS Holiday Event Research|MAM FICSMAS Holiday Event Research]] - Candy Cane Basher

metadata.name: Snowball Pile
metadata.description:
Slot: Hands
Ammo: Snowball
Disclaimer: Snowballs in pile not included in ammo reserve.
metadata.unlockedBy: [[FICSMAS Holiday Event Research|MAM FICSMAS Holiday Event Research]] - Snowball Pile

metadata.name: Portable Miner
metadata.description: Can be set up on a resource node to automatically extract the resource. Note that it has limited storage space.

metadata.name: Hover Pack
metadata.description:
Power consumption: 100 MW
Allows for vertical movement and hovering in mid-air to improve building efficiency and factory traversal. Wirelessly connects to nearby power connections, such as Power Poles and Buildings, for power consumption.
Slow-fall: Hold {PlayerMovement_Jump} after losing connection mid-air.
Disable Hoverpack: Double tap {PlayerMovement_Crouch} while hovering.

metadata.name: Hazmat Suit
metadata.description:
Shields Pioneers from the adverse effects of radiation.
Consumes Iodine Infused Filters from the inventory while worn in radioactive areas.

metadata.name: Gas Mask
metadata.description:
Allows Pioneers to breathe normally while in toxic gas areas.
Consumes Gas Filters from the inventory when in use.

metadata.name: Jetpack
metadata.description:
The Jetpack allows Pioneers to travel through the air with increased control.
Fuel is automatically consumed from the inventory to refill the Jetpack while on the ground.
Different fuel types can be used and provide different levels of Jetpack efficiency. The preferred fuel type will be used if available and can be set in the equipment inventory.

metadata.name: Chainsaw
metadata.description:
Slot: Hands
Fuel: Biofuel
Used to clear an area of flora that is too difficult to remove by hand.

metadata.name: Object Scanner
metadata.description: Scans the area for a set item. Beeps at a rate proportional to proximity and direction.

metadata.name: Rebar Gun
metadata.description: Improvised ranged weapon for self-defense. Has to be reloaded after each use.
metadata.unlockedBy: [[Alien Organisms Research|MAM Alien Organisms Research]] - The Rebar Gun

metadata.name: Rifle
metadata.description: A long-range, rapid-fire weapon. Specifically designed to deliver adequate performance within the designated work area.

metadata.name: Blade Runners
metadata.description:
An exoskeleton for the lower legs that assists movement, allowing Pioneers to sprint faster and jump higher.
Also dampens the impact of landing.

metadata.name: Zipline
metadata.description:
Provides faster traversal in factories by allowing Pioneers to zip along Power lines.
Activate the Zipline and aim at a nearby Power Line to connect to it.

metadata.name: Nobelisk Detonator
metadata.description: A remote-control device used to handle and detonate Nobelisks.
metadata.unlockedBy: [[Sulfur Research|MAM Sulfur Research]] - The Nobelisk Detonator

metadata.name: Factory Cart™
metadata.description:
The one and only FICSIT Factory Cart™
Now with special - FICSIT Foundation only - Grip Wheels, for an even smoother and faster factory floor experience!

metadata.name: Golden Factory Cart™
metadata.description:
The one and only Golden FICSIT Factory Cart™
You have now officially ascended.
Go forth now, Master of Spaghetti, God of the Factory, Sinker of Cups, Employee of the Planet... travel in STYLE!

metadata.name: Flower Petals
metadata.description:
Used for crafting.
Colorful native flower petals.

metadata.name: Wood
metadata.description:
Primarily used as fuel.
Biomass Burners and vehicles can use it for power.

Primarily used as fuel.
Biomass burners and vehicles can use it for power.
Biomass is much more energy-efficient than raw biological matter.

Used as fuel for the Nuclear Power Plant.

metadata.description:
PENDING REMOVAL
This item will (likely) be removed in a future update.
Currently only used as an ingredient in an alternative recipe.

metadata.description: Slows down your fall when activated in mid-air.

metadata.name: Stun Rebar
metadata.description:

Stun duration: 5 seconds

metadata.description: A simple iron rebar that can be shot using the Rebar Gun, for self-defense purposes.
metadata.unlockedBy: [[Alien Organisms Research|MAM Alien Organisms Research]] - The Rebar Gun

metadata.name: Homing Rifle Ammo
metadata.description:
The bullet guidance system built into this ammunition allows it to accurately hit any target within the reticle area.
Especially useful when dealing with agile threats, or for Pioneers who can't be bothered to aim properly.
metadata.unlockedBy: [[Caterium Research|MAM Caterium Research]] - Bullet Guidance System

metadata.name: Nobelisk
metadata.description: A simple explosive, useful for clearing boulders, vegetation, and other obstacles.
metadata.unlockedBy: [[Sulfur Research|MAM Sulfur Research]] - The Nobelisk Detonator

metadata.name: Cluster Nobelisk
metadata.description: A Nobelisk that detonates into multiple smaller explosions. Practical when clearing out large areas of vegetation and other inconveniences.

metadata.name: Gas Nobelisk
metadata.description: Instead of a regular explosion, this Nobelisk creates a deadly gas cloud.
metadata.unlockedBy: [[Mycelia Research|MAM Mycelia Research]] - Toxic Cellular Modification

metadata.name: Nuke Nobelisk
metadata.description:
This Nobelisk uses a nuclear fission reaction to generate a massive explosion.
WARNING: Ensure all FICSIT property is clear of the blast zone before detonation.
metadata.unlockedBy: [[Sulfur Research|MAM Sulfur Research]] - Nuclear Deterrent Development

metadata.name: Pulse Nobelisk
metadata.description: Instead of a regular explosion, this Nobelisk generates a powerful shockwave.
metadata.unlockedBy: [[Quartz Research|MAM Quartz Research]] - Explosive Resonance Application

metadata.name: Sweet Fireworks
metadata.description:
Merry FICSMAS and a Happy New Year!
Alternate Nobelisk Ammo. Use G to swap!

metadata.name: Fancy Fireworks

Fireworks are produced from random ingredients. Primarily used for having a good time.
Alternate Nobelisk Ammo. Use G to swap!

metadata.name: Sparkly Fireworks

Goes Pfffeeeeew... BOOM! *Sparkle*
Alternate Nobelisk Ammo. Use G to swap!
